@model IEnumerable<Vital.Model.NewsModel>
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Services";
}

<title>Services</title>

<div class="panel" style="background: #ededed; border: #ededed; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="twelve columns">
            <img src="~/Content/images/news.jpg" />
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="panel" style="background: #ededed; border: #ededed; margin-top: 0px; padding-top: 5px;">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="twelve columns">
            <h2 style="color: #f79020; margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 0px;">Services</h2>
            <div id="titleborder"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="four columns" style="width: 29%;">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="twelve columns">
                    <h5 style="margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 5px;"><a id="linkside1" href="~/Services/Index">Freight Brokerage</a></h5>
                    <div id="linkside1border"></div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row" style="margin-top: 0px;">
                <div class="twelve columns">
                    <h5 style="margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 5px;"><a id="linkside2" href="~/Services/Freightforwarding">Freight Forwarding</a></h5>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row" style="margin-top: 0px;">
                <div class="twelve columns">
                    <h5 style="margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 5px;"><a id="linkside2" href="~/Services/Support">Support Services</a></h5>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="eight columns" id="abtborder" style="width: 70%;">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="twelve columns" style="text-align:justify">
                    <h4 style="color: #f6a11d;">Freight Brokerage</h4>
                    Our relationships are powerful! With delivery to every postal code in Canada and to every corner of the globe, we combine the volume of our customer base to offer discounted rates. Our customers typically encounter significant savings from their existing carrier rates.
                    <br/><br/>
                    <ul id="faq" class="disc">
                        <li><p class="toggler" id="toggler-1" style="cursor:pointer; color:#f79020;">Courier</p></li>
                        <p id="widget-1" class="widget" style="display:none; margin-top: 10px;">
                            For packages up to 150lbs/68kg’s that require speed, security, tracking, specialization and individualization of express service and swift delivery times. While this is typically a more expensive option for companies, we offer our customers the best possible service at the best possible price due to our relationship with UPS who we promote as a Preferred Supplier.
                        </p>

                        <li><p id="toggler-2" class="toggler" style="cursor:pointer; color:#f79020;">Less than Truckload (LTL)</p></li>
                        <p id="widget-2" class="widget" style="display: none; margin-top: 10px;">
                            For deliveries between 151lb and 20,000lbs, we engage our preferred partners to consolidate our customers freight from various shippers onto enclosed trailers for delivery to the final destination. LTL transit times are typically longer than Full-Truck-Loads; the main advantage of using LTL is that the customer can move their freight for a fraction of the cost of hiring an entire truck and trailer.
                        </p>

                        <li><p id="toggler-3" class="toggler" style="cursor:pointer; color:#f79020;">Onboard Courier</p></li>
                        <p id="widget-3" class="widget" style="display: none; margin-top: 10px;">
                            Our onboard courier services are available to customers who require service at a moments’ notice. We engage our valued partners to deliver our customers goods via commercial airlines. Our team are experts in flight schedules, routing options, and competitive prices; we ensure that our customers most critical shipments reach their destinations in a timely and effective manner.
                        </p>

                        <li><p id="toggler-4" class="toggler" style="cursor:pointer; color:#f79020;">Direct Drive</p></li>
                        <p id="widget-4" class="widget" style="display: none; margin-top: 10px;">
                            When timing is critical Vital Logistics is the company to call for immediate transportation solutions. When a production line is going down because of a missing component or repair we understand the importance of getting that item delivered, as promised. We offer expedited road service from your location, or supplier facility to the final destination on an exclusive use basis- no other freight will be placed on the truck. A single or teamed driver will be allocated based on the distance requirement, to ensure the quickest delivery possible. All equipment types are available to meet your specific requirements including: cargo vans, cube vans, straight trucks and tractor-trailers.
                        </p>

                        </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<script>
    $(document).ready(function () {
        $('body').on('click', '.toggler', function () {
            var id = this.id.split('-');
            var myId = id[1];
            $('#widget-' + myId).focus();
            $(".widget").not("#widget-" + myId).slideUp('slow');
            $('#widget-' + myId).slideToggle('slow');
        });
    });
</script>